credibility. Instead, state facts with professional authority: "NetScript is in 
its active alpha phase (`v0.0.1-alpha.1`). View our test validation suite and 
roadmap at rickylabs.github.io/netscript/roadmap/".
+734|3. **"Fictional Dependency Graphs"**: Embedding complex ASCII diagrams or 
architecture flowcharts that do not match the actual folder workspaces or import
structures. This destroys developer confidence on first-use.
+735|4. **"Local Host and Relative Sandboxes"**: Including relative file system 
setups or dev configs (`../../my-config`) inside quickstart commands. Keep the 
quickstart isolated and standard container-runnable.
+736|5. **"Broken Image Assets"**: Linking assets via relative roots 
(`/assets/banner.png`). These render fine locally inside VSCode and GitHub, but 
break entirely on registry views of published scopes. Ensure all assets are 
served through absolute URLs hosted on GitHub Pages or CDN endpoints.
